<FONT FACE="Arial">
<P>From this table it is possible to graph the function.   R(x) = 400x is a linear function of the form f(x) = mx hence we would expect the graph to be a straight line passing through the origin (0,0) with gradient 400.</P>

<P><img src="image95.png"></P>

<br>
<P>It is now possible to estimate revenue for different values of x.</P>

<B><P>Example</P>

</B><P>For a new product the set up costs are £6500 while manufacturing costs are £150 per unit constructed.</P>

<P>The cost function can be written as</P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER">C(x) = 150x + 6500</P>

<P>This cost function is of the form f(x) = mx + c hence graphing this function we would expect a straight line passing through (0,6500) with a gradient of 150.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
